  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">KMRC Equity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Accessibility and affordability of housing finance: the proposed Project will allow KMRC to offer longer tenor funding to primary mortgage lenders in Kenya which in turn will enable primary mortgage lenders to offer longer-term mortgage loans to borrowers, ultimately increasing access and affordability of mortgages. 

Job creation: through the proposed Project, IFC will promote creation of indirect jobs through the construction of residential houses in Kenya</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project consists of an equity investment of up to US$2 million equivalent in the Kenya Mortgage Refinance Company (KMRC or the Company), of which up to US$1 million equivalent may potentially be supported by an IDA PSW Blended Finance Facility investment. KMRC is a private mortgage refinancing company that will provide long-term funding and liquidity to financial institutions to foster the development of the housing sector and improve affordability. With IDA PSW support, IFC become a shareholder and drive the impact by addressing the primary market failure of lack of access to viable financing, including in the underdeveloped counties of Garissa, Isiolo, Lamu, Mandera, Marsabit, Samburu, Tana River, Turkana, Wajir, West Pokot.</narrative>
  </description>
